gious women who have taken a vow of chastity, they mocked our God and, apart from the crucifixion, the most pivotal moment in our faith.\", \"from\": 1047, \"to\": 1318, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1167, \"end\": 1176, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.993863193773108e-18, \"text\": \"Catholics\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The moment he offers his body, soul and divinity, as a perpetual gift for his friends and followers for time immemorial.\", \"from\": 1319, \"to\": 1439, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In an A+ display of gaslighting, the Olympic Committee tweeted out an image of the perverse display and said, \\\"Olympics: The interpretation of the Greek God Dionysus makes us aware of the absurdity of violence between human beings.\\\"\", \"from\": 1441, \"to\": 1673, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1588, \"end\": 1593, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\", \"score\": 0.855010139673409, \"rank\": 0.16203038160737496, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\"}, {\"begin\": 1598, \"end\": 1606, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.92216804602466e-32, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There is the issue with the fact that Dionysus, while primarily the god of wine and pleasure, was also known to, quite literally, tear his enemies to pieces.\", \"from\": 1675, \"to\": 1832, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1713, \"end\": 1721, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"