atholic violence in France appears to be committed not by radical Muslims, but by radical secularists.\", \"from\": 2599, \"to\": 2723, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2615, \"end\": 2637, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anti-Catholicism\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"anti-Catholic violence\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anti-Catholicism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anti-Catholicism\"}, {\"begin\": 2641, \"end\": 2647, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999928835958067, \"rank\": 7.103287525744752e-06, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2687, \"end\": 2694, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\", \"score\": 0.9979748414504399, \"rank\": 0.0020292670613811297, \"text\": \"Muslims\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They have set countless churches on fire, vandalized statues and holy buildings, desecrated tabernacles, and scrawled blasphemy and threats on ancient edifices like \\\"blessed abortion\\\" on the walls of Saint-Jacques Church in Grenoble and \\\"our lives, our bodies belong to us\\\" on The Cathedral of Saint-Jean of Besan\\u00e7on and \\\"Satan punishes homophobes\\\" on Toulouse's Saint-Roch-du-F\\u00e9r\\u00e9tra Chapel.\", \"from\": 2724, \"to\": 3116, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2924, \"end\": 2937, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint-Jacques-du-Haut-Pas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.183502247274003e-20, \"text\": \"Saint-Jacques\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint-Jacques-du-Haut-Pas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint-Jacques-du-Haut-Pas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Not long after vandals wrote \\\"blessed abortion\\\" on the walls of Saint-Jacques Church in Grenoble, they burned it to the ground.\", \"from\": 3118, \"to\": 3245, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3182, \"end\": 3195, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint-Jacques-du-Haut-Pas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.183502247274003e-20, \"text\": \"Saint-Jacques\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint-Jacques-du-Haut-Pas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint-Jacques-du-Haut-Pas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"PARIS OLYMPICS IN FULL SWING AS ORGANIZERS NAVIGATE FALLOUT OF OPENING CEREMONY UPROAR  Attacks onCatholic churchesin France are hardly isolated incidents, but rather a part of a troubling continental trend.\", \"from\": 3247, \"to\": 3454, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3365, \"end\": 3371, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999928835958067, \"rank\": 7.103287525744752e-06, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Observatory on Intolerance and Discrimination Against Christians in Europe (OIDAC) found that anti-Christian hate crimes rose 44 percent just between the year 2021 and 2022.\", \"from\": 3455, \"to\": 3632, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3513, \"end\": 3523, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9997126939716983, \"rank\": 0.00028188995363994355, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 3553, \"end\": 3567, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antichrist\", \"score\": 0.9259616657252874, \"rank\": 0.07993440821422754, \"text\": \"anti-Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antichrist\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antichrist\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Arson attacks were up by a stunning 75 percent.\", \"from\": 3633, \"to\": 3680, \"entities\": [{\"begin\